<div class="left_main_content">
<h2 class="section_heading">Internships give students hands-on training in their chosen fields.</h2>
<img alt="Internships" class="left_main_content_image" height="196" src="Images/Twin Pillars/Intern_Construction.jpg" width="274" />
<p>One of the best ways to learn is by doing. To truly master a discipline, students need the opportunity to take what that they've learned in the classroom and use it in a real-world setting. That's why internships are an integral part of a BYU-Idaho education. BYU-Idaho is one of the largest intern-providing institutions in the nation, with students fanning out across the globe each semester to work with internship providers and gain practical experience.</p>
<p>These hands-on opportunities enable students to receive valuable work experience with qualified professionals. Once students see how a company operates and what is required to succeed in their field, they gain a practical view of their career choice. Statistics show that nearly 50 percent of students receive a job offer at the completion of their internship.</p>
<p>Many employers seek out BYU-Idaho students because of their strong work ethic, creativity, and professional demeanor. Internship providers are also eager to work with BYU-Idaho students because they are available year round, thanks to the university's unique Three-Track System.</p>
